  Session Summary — 17 June 2026
Problem: Couldn't sign in. Server returned 500 on /api/auth/signin.
Root Cause: After consolidating secrets into a single .env.production file (June 14), PM2 was starting the Next.js server directly without loading that file. DATABASE_URL was empty, Prisma couldn't connect, every request 500'd. PM2 6.0.14 silently ignored env_file in ecosystem config.
Fix: Created a wrapper script that sources .env.production with set -a before launching Node. PM2 runs the script, env vars flow through to the child process. No secrets exposed, no hardcoding, survives restarts. Made persistent with pm2 save.
Secondary: Deploy Pipeline Fixed: Build output structure had changed — standalone directory no longer produced. Deploy now copies .next directly from source to production. Ownership issue fixed.
